Mogens C. Bay 

		
		Chairman and CEO, 

	
		 Valmont Industries Inc. 	

 
Last Updated: 01/30/2016 



Executive Summary
Bay is Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Valmont Industries Inc., one of the world's leading providers of engineered products and services for infrastructure, and irrigation equipment for agriculture.  He joined the Omaha, Nebraska-based company in 1979 as Regional Vice President for Southeast Asia. Aft 
Personal Attributes and Interests

Bay and his wife, Cindy, have a daughter, Sarah, and three grandsons, Charlie, Henry and Alexander. They all live in Omaha, Nebraska.
In 2013, Bay was inducted into Omaha Chamber Business Hall of Fame. 
Current Focus

Company Snapshot: Valmont Industries Inc., based in Omaha, Nebraska, is one of the world's leading providers of engineered products and services for infrastructure, and irrigation equipment for agriculture. The com 
Key Challenges

Profit Plunge Leads to Layoffs: Sharply lower profits have prompted Valmont Industries to cut around 700 jobs in the last six months, or more than 6% of the total workforce of about 11,300 it counted at the end of last 
Biographical Highlights

Born January, 1949 in Vejle,  Denmark.
Bay earned a law degree from Aarhus University in 1970. 
Other Boards and Organizations

Former Secretary and Director, Nebraska Medical Center
Former Member, Advisory Board, Nebraska Medicine 
 





